    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: 0.4.2 and up\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? Yes\r\n- Operating system/version: Arch Linux\r\n- Terminal name/version: Tilix 1.9.3 and GNOME Terminal 3.34 (vte3 0.58)\r\n- `$TERM`: screen-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\nCan't be reproduced with `nvim -u NORC`. Can be reproduced with a minimal configuration file, as outlined in the section below.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nWhen neovim starts up, the lines and columns are restricted to 24Ã—80. It doesn't do this if you start with `nvim -u NORC`. I've been trying to figure out _why_ this is happening, and have disabled all plugins and reduced my configuration down to this:\r\n\r\n    if &compatible\r\n    \tset nocompatible\r\n    endif\r\n    if has('vim_starting')\r\n    \tset all&\r\n    endif\r\n\r\n    augroup vimrc\r\n    \tau!\r\n    augroup END\r\n\r\n    let g:mapleader = '\\'\r\n    let g:maplocalleader = '\\'\r\n\r\n    let g:loaded_netrw = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_netrwPlugin = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_netrwFileHandlers = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_netrwSettings = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_vimball = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_vimballPlugin = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_zip = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_zipPlugin = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_tutor_mode_plugin = 1\r\n    let g:loaded_2html_plugin = 1\r\n\r\n    set nowrap\r\n    set linebreak\r\n    set breakat=\\ \\\t;:,!?\r\n    set nostartofline\r\n    set whichwrap+=h,l,<,>,[,],~\r\n    set splitbelow splitright\r\n    set switchbuf=useopen,usetab\r\n    set switchbuf+=vsplit\r\n    set backspace=indent,eol,start\r\n    set diffopt=filler,iwhite\r\n    set tags=.git/tags,tags\r\n    set showfulltag\r\n    set complete=.\r\n    set completeopt=menuone\r\n    set completeopt+=noselect\r\n    set virtualedit=block\r\n    \"set report=0\r\n    set magic\r\n    set modeline\r\n    \"set modelines=5\r\n    set mouse=a\r\n    set mousehide\r\n    set hidden\r\n    set autoread\r\n    set fileformats+=unix,dos,mac\r\n    set nrformats=octal,hex,alpha\r\n    set noerrorbells\r\n    set novisualbell\r\n    \"set textwidth=0\r\n    \"set tabstop=4\r\n    \"set softtabstop=4\r\n    \"set shiftwidth=4\r\n    set smarttab\r\n    set autoindent\r\n    set smartindent\r\n    set noexpandtab\r\n    set shiftround\r\n    set nolist\r\n    set timeout ttimeout\r\n    \"set timeoutlen=1000\r\n    \"set updatetime=1000\r\n    \"set ttimeoutlen=-1\r\n    set hlsearch\r\n    set incsearch\r\n    set ignorecase\r\n    set smartcase\r\n    set wrapscan\r\n    set showmatch\r\n    set matchpairs+=<:>\r\n    \"set matchtime=1\r\n    set cpoptions-=m\r\n    if has('wildmenu')\r\n    \tset wildmenu\r\n    \tset wildmode=list:longest,full\r\n    \tset wildoptions=tagfile\r\n    \tset wildignorecase\r\n    \tset wildignore+=.hg,.git,.svn\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.aux,*.out\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.jpg,*.bmp,*.gif,*.png,*.jpeg\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.o,*.obj,*.exe,*.dll,*.manifest\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.spl\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.sw?\r\n    \tset wildignore+=.DS_Store\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.luac\r\n    \tset wildignore+=*.pyc\r\n    endif\r\n    set sessionoptions-=blank\r\n    set sessionoptions-=options\r\n    set sessionoptions-=globals\r\n    set sessionoptions-=help\r\n    set sessionoptions+=tabpages\r\n    set viewoptions-=options\r\n    set viewoptions-=unix,slash\r\n\r\nThe offending lines (that I've been able to find through a process of elimination) are commented out above. Why any of those lines should cause this weird issue is beyond me, as they're perfectly normal options to set.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2019-09-20 20-32-12](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/172912/65321736-549d4780-dbe8-11e9-9a16-eab2f7c03c1c.png)\r\n\r\nThere's probably a whole lot more. My configuration, including plugins, is rather complex, and I keep discovering new ones as I add lines into the test init.vim I've been building up.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nNeovim should fill the terminal window.\r\n\r\n",
