        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Can reproduce. It used to be worse though, before #10959 nvim would get stuck with the old size if it was resized while a message (like swap dialog) was shown (even after the message was dismissed). With master I can reproduce it using `nvim --cmd \"lua os.execute('sleep 3')\"` (and resize before 3 seconds), as a proxy for anything that blocks CPU without processing events. The resize event should only be delayed in this case, not dropped entirely.\r\n",
